CSS means Cascading Style sheet.
CSS are used to apply style to the html tags.
  
Element Selector: Targets all elements of a specific type.
p {
  color: blue;
  back ground-Image="";
  back ground colour="";
  
  
}
ID Selector: Targets a single element with a specific id.
#header {
  background-color: yellow;
}
Class Selector: Targets all elements with a specific class.

.container {
  width: 100%;
}
Universal Selector: Targets all elements.

* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
Combinator Selectors
Descendant Selector: Selects all elements that are descendants of a specified element.

div p {
  color: red;
}
Child Selector: Selects all elements that are direct children of a specified element.

div > p {
  color: green;
}
Adjacent Sibling Selector: Selects an element that is immediately preceded by a specified element.

h1 + p {
  color: purple;
}
General Sibling Selector: Selects all elements that are siblings of a specified element.

h1 ~ p {
  color: orange;
}
Attribute Selectors
[attribute]: Selects elements with a specified attribute.

a[target] {
  color: blue;
}
[attribute="value"]: Selects elements with a specific attribute value.

input[type="text"] {
  border: 1px solid #000;
}
[attribute^="value"]: Selects elements with an attribute value starting with a specified value.

a[href^="https"] {
  color: green;
}
[attribute$="value"]: Selects elements with an attribute value ending with a specified value.

a[href$=".pdf"] {
  color: red;
}
*[attribute="value"]**: Selects elements with an attribute value containing a specified value.

a[href*="example"] {
  color: purple;
}
Pseudo-Class Selectors
:hover: Targets an element when the mouse hovers over it.

a:hover {
  color: orange;
}
:first-child: Targets the first child element within a parent.

p:first-child {
  font-weight: bold;
}
:last-child: Targets the last child element within a parent.

p:last-child {
  font-style: italic;
}
:nth-child(n): Targets the nth child element within a parent.

li:nth-child(2) {
  color: red;
}
Pseudo-Element Selectors
::before: Inserts content before an element's content.

p::before {
  content: "Note: ";
  font-weight: bold;
}
::after: Inserts content after an element's content.
p::after {
  content: ".";
}
::first-line: Styles the first line of an element.

p::first-line {
  color: blue;
  font-weight: bold;
}
::first-letter: Styles the first letter of an element.

p::first-letter {
  font-size: 2em;
  color: red;
}
